-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
AGPLv3 tool to create networks of kvm virtual machines or crun containers
connected through the openvswitch software.
See directory cloonix for the LICENCE
See clownix.net for a documentation (usually not up to date).
http://clownix.net/doc_stored/build-24-00/html/index.html doc.

NOTE: qemu-guest-agent sometimes called qemu-ga has to be installed
      inside the kvm guests to have the best of cloonix.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DOWNLOADS:

http://clownix.net/downloads/cloonix-24-00

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
THIS SOFTWARE HAS BEEN COMPILED AND TESTED ON:

            jammy   (ubuntu 22.04),
            impish  (ubuntu 21.10),
            hirsute (ubuntu 21.05),
            bookworm (debian 12),
            bullseye (debian 11),
            tumbleweed (rolling opensuse),
            fedora35

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALL CLOONIX ON YOUR HOST:

wget http://clownix.net/downloads/cloonix-24-00/cloonix-24-00.tar.gz
tar xvf cloonix-24-00.tar.gz
cd cloonix-24-00
sudo ./install_depends

wget http://clownix.net/downloads/cloonix-24-00/targz_store.tar.gz
tar xvf targz_store.tar.gz

./doitall

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
FOR KVM GET A WORKING QCOW AND PUT IT IN BULK:

wget http://clownix.net/downloads/cloonix-24-00/bulk/bookworm.qcow2.gz

mkdir -p ${HOME}/cloonix_data/bulk
cp bookworm.qcow2.gz ${HOME}/cloonix_data/bulk
cd ${HOME}/cloonix_data/bulk
gunzip bookworm.qcow2.gz

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
FOR CRUN GET A WORKING IMG AND PUT IT IN BULK:

wget http://clownix.net/downloads/cloonix-24-00/bulk/bookworm.img.gz
cp bookworm.img.gz ${HOME}/cloonix_data/bulk
cd ${HOME}/cloonix_data/bulk
gunzip bookworm.img.gz

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
LAUNCH KVM EXAMPLE:

cd cloonix/quickstart
./ping_kvm.sh

On the gui, a double-click on the blue machine gives a shell,
a double-click on the green interface gives a wireshark spy,
a right-click on the blue machine gives a spice desktop.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
LAUNCH CRUN EXAMPLE:

For a quick test, you need the sudo program to elevate privileges to
root level with no password for crun control.

cd cloonix/quickstart
./ping_crun.sh

On the gui, a double-click on the blue machine gives a shell,
a double-click on the green interface gives a wireshark spy.

Note: openwrt is special, it has ash instead of bash and it does
not turn blue because the libc is different. TODO

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CREATION OF THE QCOW2 AND IMG FILES:

cd cloonix/quickstart/create_kvm/ for qcow2
cd cloonix/quickstart/create_crun/ for img 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
TEST OF CISCO FEATURE:

cd cloonix/quickstart/cisco

